<article>
    <h1>VA&#xAD;LEN&#xAD;CIA UN&#xAD;DER PETER LIM</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20200813/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-08-13"><time>2020-08-13</time></a>
        - <span>SPORT</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>They last won the league in 2004; last ma­jor hon­our was the 2008 Span­ish Cup. From 2008 to 2013, the club fin­ished 10th, sixth, third, third, third and fifth in the league.</p>
    <p>2014 Peter Lim takes over Va­len­cia for €100 mil­lion (S$162 mil­lion) 2015 4th in La Liga, qual­i­fied for Cham­pi­ons League 2016 12th, knocked out in Cham­pi­ons League group stage, reached Europa League last 16</p>
    <p>2017 12th 2018 4th, qual­i­fied for Cham­pi­ons League</p>
    <p>2019 4th, qual­i­fied for Cham­pi­ons League, knocked out in Cham­pi­ons League group stage, reached Europa League semi-fi­nals 2020 9th, reached Cham­pi­ons League round of 16</p>
    <p>MAN­AGE­RIAL CHANGES</p>
    <p>Since 2014, Va­len­cia have hired eight man­agers – Sal­vador Gon­za­lez stepped in as care­taker on four oc­ca­sions.</p>
    <p>TRANS­FERS</p>
    <p>(Ac­cord­ing to trans­fer­markt)</p>
    <p>2014-15 €53.3m (bought) and €55.5m (sold) 2015-16 €143.9m (bought) and €50m (sold) 2016-17 €36m (bought) and €114.9m (sold) 2017-18 €55m (bought) and €16.6m (sold) 2018-19 €129.2m (bought) and €68.8m (sold) 2019-20 €75m (bought) and €56.3m (sold)</p>
    <p>WHY FANS ARE UN­HAPPY</p>
    <p>• Ac­cuse Peter Lim and pres­i­dent Anil Murthy of “neg­li­gently man­ag­ing the club”, “de­te­ri­o­rat­ing the value of the team” and “mis­treat­ing old leg­ends and club work­ers”.</p>
    <p>• Re­moval of ex- man­ager Marcelino, who led the club to the King’s Cup, fourth place in La Liga and Cham­pi­ons League qual­i­fi­ca­tion last year.</p>
    <p>• Re­moval of team del­e­gate Paco Ca­ma­rasa, who has been at the club for four decades.</p>
    <p>• Sale of Francis Co­quelin and Dani Parejo to Vil­lar­real.</p>


